docs.lead_paragraph: The general death rate for New York City in the week ended last Saturday declined to 8.9 per 1,000 population, lower than ever before at this time of year, it was reported yesterday to Dr. John L. Rice, City Health Commissioner, by Thomas J. Duffield, Registrar of Records.

headline.main: DEATH RATE IN CITY DROPS DESPITE COLD; Lower Last Week Than Ever Before at This Time of Year
